===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|broun|lang=enm|sc=Latn}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|brun|brūn|lang=ang|dark, shining}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|brūnaz|lang=gem-pro}} (compare {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|brún|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|bruin|lang=nl}}, German {{term|braun|lang=de}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|bʰruHnos|lang=ine-pro}} (compare Ancient Greek {{term||lang=grc|tr=phrýnē}}, {{term|||lang=grc|tr=phrŷnos|toad}}), enlargement of {{recons|bʰrew-||shiny, brown|lang=ine-pro}} (compare {{etyl|lt|-}} {{term|beras|bė́ras|lang=lt|brown}}, Sanskrit {{term|||tr=babhrú|reddish-brown|lang=sa}} {{rfscript|Devanagari|lang=sa}}).

